We have now to consider the nature ol species as existing in the medium. Many have regarded it as body. But this is misleading. To speak ol it as body would imply that it was something which divided the surrounding medium, having three dimensione of its own. But the species has no dimensions other than those of the medium in which it is generated. During the generation ot' species from the medium, the medium does not lose its corporeal character, nor is any new body created or added. The species is simply a portion of the medium wrought on in a peculiar way hythe agent.
